This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by the White House Office of the Press Secretary on May 4, 2010. The memorandum is titled "United States-India Nuclear Cooperation Approval and Nonproliferation Enhancement Act" and it delegates certain functions under section 201(b) of this act to the Secretary of Energy. The President, Barack Obama, delegates the certification and reporting functions to the Secretary of Energy and authorizes them to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.